verblex: 1. To be located at the side or part of something that is towards the rear or farthest from the front. English = at the back of.
2. To move in a direction which is the opposite direction to the one in which you normally face or in which you normally go. English = go backwards, back up, reverse.
3. To move in a direction that takes you to a place where you were before. English = go back.
nomlex: 1. The side or part of something that is towards the rear or farthest from the front. It is normally not used or seen as much as the front. English = back.
2. The kind of family you come from and the kind of education you have had. English = background.
